{"id":"7890","name":"Convert Color to Hex [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to convert any color to its \"#RRGGBB\" or \"#RRGGBBAA\" representation","icon":"ios15 c255 g59716","latest":"33348","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A single line of JavaScript to get the \"#RRGGBB\" or \"#RRGGBBAA\" representation of any color you need. It can be used to normalize color representation, to get a filename-safe value to avoid having to do color tables or hexadecimal conversions.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Non-valid inputs return <code>#000000</code></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20pipette%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20convert%20any%20color%20to%20its%20%5C%22%23RRGGBB%5C%22%20or%20%5C%22%23RRGGBBAA%5C%22%20representation%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20%282020-12-25%29%5Cn%5Cn-%20Examples%20of%20valid%20colors%3A%20red%2C%20%23257ABD%2C%20rgb%28255%2C%200%2C%20255%29%2C%20hsl%2890%2C%20100%25%2C%2050%25%29%2C%20%23FF7F007F%2C%20rgb%28255%200%20255%20%2F%200.5%29%2C%20hwb%28194%200%25%200%25%20%2F%2050%25%29%2C%20transparent%5Cn-%20v2%20%282022-05-31%29%20changes%20the%20output%20from%20rgb%28%29%2Frgba%28%29%20to%20hexadecimal%2C%20works%20now%20as%20a%20function%2C%20and%20drops%20compatibility%20with%20iOS%2012%5Cn-%20Non-valid%20inputs%20return%20%E2%80%98%23000000%E2%80%99%22%0AText%20rebeccapurple%20-%3E%20mv%3AText%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%3Bcharset%3Dutf-8%2C%3Cbody%20style%3D%27color%3A%5C%28mv%3AText%29%27%3E%3Cscript%3Ewith%28document%29write%28eval%28getComputedStyle%28body%29.color.replace%28%2Frgba%3F%5C%5C%28%28.%2B%3F%29%2C%20%28.%2B%3F%29%2C%20%28.%2B%3F%29%28%3F%3A%2C%20%28.%2B%3F%29%29%3F%5C%5C%29%2F%2C%5C%22%27%23%27%2B%28%28%241%2A256%2B%242%29%2A256%2B%243%29.toString%2816%29.padStart%286%2C0%29%2B%28%27%244%27%3FMath.round%28%27%244%27%2A255.4%29.toString%2816%29.padStart%282%2C0%29%3A%27%27%29%5C%22%29%29%29%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%0AGetFileofType%20%22com.apple.webarchive%22%20-%3E%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%0AShowAlert%20title%3Dmv%3AText%20message%3D%22%5C%28mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%29%22%20showCancelButton%3Dfalse\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/Window/getComputedStyle\"><code>window.getComputedStyle</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The color can be any <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/CSS/color\">valid CSS color value</a>. Examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>red</li>\n<li>#257ABD</li>\n<li>rgb(255, 0, 255)</li>\n<li>hsl(90, 100%, 50%)</li>\n<li>#FF7F007F</li>\n<li>rgb(255 0 255 / 0.5)</li>\n<li>hwb(194 0% 0% / 50%)</li>\n<li>transparent</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html;charset=utf-8,&lt;body style='color:REPLACETHISWITHCOLORVARIABLE'&gt;&lt;script&gt;with(document)write(eval(getComputedStyle(body).color.replace(/rgba?\\((.+?), (.+?), (.+?)(?:, (.+?))?\\)/,\"'#'+(($1*256+$2)*256+$3).toString(16).padStart(6,0)+('$4'?Math.round('$4'*255.4).toString(16).padStart(2,0):'')\")))&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Replace the <code>REPLACETHISWITHCOLORVARIABLE</code> fragment with the variable containing the color, and add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below to get \"#RRGGBB\" or \"#RRGGBBAA\" representation of the color.</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>2.0.0 - May 31, 2022, 10:49 a.m.</strong></p><p>Changes the output from rgb()/rgba() to hexadecimal, works now as a function, and drops compatibility with iOS 12 (although an equivalent shortcut for iOS 12 can be generated from ScPL). It should work in iOS 13/14 but I haven't been able to test it.</p>"}